<div class="grid lg:grid-cols-3 gap-10">
  <div class="lg:col-span-2 space-y-8">
    <p class="text-slate-600 leading-relaxed">Aberdeen's Transit-Oriented Development (TOD) Plan establishes a long-range vision for walkable, mixed-use development in the area surrounding the Aberdeen MARC commuter rail station. The plan aims to leverage the station's connectivity to Baltimore and Washington DC to attract investment, housing, and commercial activity to downtown Aberdeen.</p>

    <div>
      <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-navy mb-4">TOD Vision</h2>
      <div class="grid sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
        {% for item in [
          { title: "Mixed-Use Development", desc: "A blend of residential, retail, office, and civic uses within walking distance of the MARC station." },
          { title: "Walkability", desc: "Pedestrian-friendly streets, connections, and public spaces linking the station to downtown." },
          { title: "Housing Diversity", desc: "A range of housing types to serve Aberdeen's growing and diverse population." },
          { title: "Economic Growth", desc: "New commercial investment and job creation anchored by transit access." },
          { title: "Placemaking", desc: "High-quality public spaces and streetscapes that create a vibrant downtown identity." },
          { title: "Sustainable Design", desc: "Green building practices, stormwater management, and reduced car dependency." }
        ] %}
        <div class="bg-white border border-slate-200 rounded-xl p-4">
          <h3 class="text-sm font-bold text-navy mb-1">{{ item.title }}</h3>
          <p class="text-xs text-slate-600">{{ item.desc }}</p>
        </div>
        {% endfor %}
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-gov-blue-light rounded-xl p-6">
      <h2 class="text-lg font-bold text-navy mb-3">Aberdeen MARC Station</h2>
      <p class="text-sm text-slate-700 mb-4">Aberdeen is served by the MARC Penn Line, providing direct commuter rail service to Baltimore Penn Station and Washington Union Station. This connectivity is a key asset for attracting residents and businesses to the TOD area.</p>
      <div class="grid sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4 text-sm">
